element.name: War Memorial Park by Kili or bust, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit The Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

element.long-description:
This is a lovely and not so overused park, close to the centre of Dublin. There is a peaceful stretch of the river Liffey and most times you can witness boat crews out practising.
The park is at the Phoenix Park end of South Circular Road and can be reached easily by any means, bus, bicycle, on foot from town or by car.
Parking is available at 53 20.751N 006 18.584W which is outside the park or at 53 20.749N 006 18.806W which will bring you into it. Be sure to watch for the time this car park closes which is posted there. In March when this cache was placed the closing time was 4.00 pm.
Go to the South West exit from the Memorial area.
The cache has been changed to a micro at 21/7/07 and also has been move up a few feet to escape the water.
element.encoded-hints: Cache has been moved a few feet. It is now about knee height on left as you ascend behind small pointed stone.

2010-05-09T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by AbbeyAckbar
2nd dnf today. Great park. I won't mind coming back here to look for the cache and with Ackbar next time.

2010-04-25T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by anacreon
Spent about 20 minutes looking for something matching the hint; given the log history it doesn't sound that hard to find, but I was unhappy picking apart a stone wall. There are already some gaps and fallen stones, so it might have been accidentally uncovered.
